Marcela, the leader of this group, is an old and skilled entrepreneur who's been selling tennis and slippers in Chacuey Abajo, a low-income community of Cotuí. Her experience and knowledge of the market have allowed her to do her work successfully, in spite of the hard competition. Her clients are satisfied with her good quality and low-priced products.
This loan is to invest in a new collection of fashionable shoes and slippers that are in high demand in the community.  Marcela says that satisfying her customers is the key to her success. So, she has to pay constant attention to her clients' demands, and when her patrons ask for a certain item she adds it in her inventory. Marcela hopes that this loan will allow her to strengthen her business and improve her family's lifestyle.
<p>The members of Marcela's group are:
Felicia H., who sells fried dishes;
Paulina J. C., who sells sweets and candies;
and Valentina R., who sells beauty products;
The photo shows from left to right: Valentina, Paulina, Marcela and Felicia.
